/android/app/release

# Firebase client configs — real configs contain Google API keys flagged by
# GitHub secret scanning. Both platforms' files are gitignored; CI injects
# them from repo secrets GOOGLE_SERVICES_JSON (Android) and
# GOOGLE_SERVICE_INFO_PLIST (iOS). For local builds, download from
# Firebase Console into:
#   android/app/src/prod/google-services.json
#   ios/Runner/GoogleService-Info.plist
# Android dev/staging flavors skip the google-services plugin (see
# android/app/build.gradle.kts) so Android non-prod works without the file.
# iOS dev/staging strip the plist from the built .app at build time (see
# Runner.xcodeproj :: "Strip Firebase plist" phase), but Xcode's Copy
# Bundle Resources still needs the file to exist locally — CI seeds a
# minimal placeholder; local devs keep their real prod plist in place.
android/app/src/prod/google-services.json
ios/Runner/GoogleService-Info.plist
